nodes.bodyText:
It's not completely ignored. The following code prints 1322842530 and 1322842529 respecively.
    System.out.println(Instant.from(DateTimeFormatter.ISO_DATE_TIME.parse("2011-12-03T01:15:30+09:00:00")).getEpochSecond());
    System.out.println(Instant.from(DateTimeFormatter.ISO_DATE_TIME.parse("2011-12-03T01:15:30+09:00:01")).getEpochSecond());
However, I don't really think anyone will really use seconds (other than 00) as part of timezone.

